com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata

Class MarketDataIFIXMessageFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata.MarketDataIFIXMessageFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMarketDataMessageFactory

    public class MarketDataIFIXMessageFactory
extends Object
implements IMarketDataMessageFactory
    IMarketDataMessageFactory implementation based on an underlying IFIXMessageFactory and "decorator" classes wrapping messages generated by that underlying factory.

    The decorator classes used in this factory are designed to expose the underlying FIX message data only through the ITagValueIterableFromTag.iterator() method. This is particularly suitable for sending FAST encoded messages.

    Only header fields and other unchanging fields ae stored in the underlying FIX message. These fields may be directly accessed using the standard IFIXMessage getValue methods. However, the changing MDEntry fields are not stored in the underlying FIX messages, and are therefore not accessible using the getValue methods. These dynamic message fields are only accessible when returned through as ITagValue's returned by ITagValueIterableFromTag.iterator().

    Currently this factory should only be used when FAST encoding is being used to send messages. With the existing underlying Session code, messages returned by this factory will not send correctly over a non FAST encoded Session.

    Author:
    John Cameron
